710322f-c.text:
Ninth Avenue (elevated line thereon), south from W. 17th (left) Street. Below same and occupying an entire square block is the mammouth Port of N.Y. Authority Building. View No. 3 shows the westerly portion of same on the eastern side of the
Avenue between 16th and 15th Streets.
No. 2 is an eastward view on 17th Street, showing structures at the S.E. and N.E. corners. To the left of the latter is a vacant lot which has recently been cleared. Upon this site will be erected a new 6 story apartment according to the New York Times of May 9, 1938. This is the S.E. corner of W. 18th
Street.
June 15, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3
P. L. Sperr

711416f-a.text:
(1) 401-407 West 17th Street, west of, adjoining, and at the N.W. corner of Ninth Avenue.  Nos. 401 and 407 are three-story, No. 405 is a four-story and No. 409 is a two-story frame house. 1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York, Negative No. 183

(2) The Same and showing a more complete view.  The frame building at the N.W. corner bears No's. 401 W. 17th Street, and 111 Ninth Ave. June 11, 1935.
P.L. Sperr
